<subSubSection id="E3620CEC77CACD44093CD9F5C5A27E67" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" type="note">
<paragraph id="7C5E28A05F7A39BB8BF9FD6D503EEB02" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA9B97DC2BAB04996C4B1294BD4A78A0" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
According to the molecular phylogenies presented by 
<bibRefCitation id="660D34A55775B6912B5F79E9891D02FC" author="Heinrichs, J" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="1" pageNumber="14" pagination="973 - 985" publicationUrl="10.1016/j.ympev.2011.11.029" refId="B2" refString="Heinrichs, J, Bombosch, A, Feldberg, K, Kreier, HP, Hentschel, J, Eckstein, J, Long, D, Zhu, RL, Schaefer-Verwimp, A, Schmidt, AR, Shaw, B, Shaw, AJ, Vana, J, 2012. A phylogeny of the northern temperate leafy liverwort genus Scapania (Scapaniaceae, Jungermanniales). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 62: 973 - 985, 10.1016/j.ympev.2011.11.029" title="A phylogeny of the northern temperate leafy liverwort genus Scapania (Scapaniaceae, Jungermanniales)." url="10.1016/j.ympev.2011.11.029" volume="62" year="2012">Heinrichs et al. (2012)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E98870EC0F3D0BCB85380DD83BF271B1" authorityName="sect. Simmonsia (R. M. Schust.) Vana, Hentschel, Joch. Muell. &amp; Heinrichs" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="sect. Simmonsia (R. M. Schust.) Vana, Hentschel, Joch. Muell. &amp; Heinrichs" baseAuthorityYear="2012" class="Hepaticae" family="Scapaniaceae" genus="Scapania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D1E8137E2579DD67709CE2C3C003CDFC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Scapania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sect. 
<emphasis id="3FFB722587473CD11CC10D521A2CF930" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Gracilidae</emphasis>
forms a lineage outside 
<emphasis id="2AE4188C52F2C8FBCC7954E6BBFC25E3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Scapania</emphasis>
subg. 
<taxonomicName id="262150275A6462A1864F7BB32B0729CF" authorityName="sect. Simmonsia (R. M. Schust.) Vana, Hentschel, Joch. Muell. &amp; Heinrichs" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="sect. Simmonsia (R. M. Schust.) Vana, Hentschel, Joch. Muell. &amp; Heinrichs" baseAuthorityYear="2012" class="Hepaticae" family="Scapaniaceae" genus="Scapania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="95AA37239F4A3BDA3B870F8727E8BDF2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Scapania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; hence, we propose subgenus rank (
<figureCitation id="4022006B48FEDD52879782732C4C6A14" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Phylogeny of Scapania with the new taxa indicated in bold. Modified from Heinrichs et al. (2012, Fig. 1)." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10032" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
